# Pagination Implementation Summary

I've successfully implemented pagination across the list endpoints for the Todos API.

## Changes Made

### 1. Standardized Pagination Response Metadata
Added a standard `PaginationMeta` struct to `backend/dto/response.go`:
```go
type PaginationMeta struct {
	TotalItems  int `json:"total_items"`
	TotalPages  int `json:"total_pages"`
	CurrentPage int `json:"current_page"`
	Limit       int `json:"limit"`
}
```

### 2. Service Layer Pagination Helper
Added a generic `paginate` helper function in `backend/services/todo_service.go`. This helper safely creates page slices from fully filtered/sorted memory slices and auto-generates the `PaginationMeta`. 

> [!TIP]
> Using a generic `[T any]` allowed the pagination helper to seamlessly work for both `[]models.Todo` (groups and subtasks) and `[]models.GroupShare` (shared groups).

### 3. API Enhancements
Updated the `TodoService` and following Controllers to accept `page` and `limit` queries (defaulting to page 1 and limit 10), and embed the metadata inside a new `meta` object in the JSON responses:
- **`GetGroups`** in [group_controller.go](file:///d:/Todo%20KreditBee/backend/controllers/group_controller.go)
- **`GetSubtasks`** in [subtask_controller.go](file:///d:/Todo%20KreditBee/backend/controllers/subtask_controller.go)
- **`GetSharedGroups`** in [share_controller.go](file:///d:/Todo%20KreditBee/backend/controllers/share_controller.go)

